column5:
It sounds to me like severe bullying, which of course can be abuse. I think you should work on separating yourself from her if she brings you down. You matter so much more than people's opinions on you. Don't go to school thinking of how other people will treat your experience, go for your own reasons. Go because you want to put in your effort, whether it be d's or c's. At the end of the day you can tell yourself you tried, and if other people can't see that then that doesn't have to be your problem.

&#x200B;

I'm also on Ritalin so, Ritalin buddies :'D
